<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">The unit pivots today. From science to assessment. The IPCC enters the conversation.</p>
  <p>The IPCC (Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change) is not a research paper. It's a <strong>synthesis</strong> — every 6-8 years, hundreds of scientists summarise thousands of papers into a report that policymakers can act on. Today: how the IPCC works, what its working groups do, what "SSP scenarios" mean (SSP1-1.9 through SSP5-8.5), and what the confidence-level language ("likely" / "very likely" / "virtually certain") actually means in probability terms.</p>
  <p>The <strong>OPVL move on AR6 figures</strong> is different from OPVL on a single news article. AR6 figures synthesise hundreds of model runs across multiple scenarios. The Origin is "IPCC AR6 WG1"; the Purpose is "inform policymakers"; the Value is "current scientific consensus on uncertainty ranges"; the Limitation is "models can't predict specific local events, only project ensemble behaviour under specific assumptions." Today's the day to internalise that move.</p>
  <p>Today is also the day the <a href="/units/unit-4/assessment-chennai-climate-brief/">Chennai Climate Brief</a> is assigned. The 8 adaptation challenges are released. Policy Panel format previewed. From this block forward, every U4 activity feeds the Brief.</p>
</section>

